<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="543" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,574]" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,330,356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is a large species and characterized as follows:characteristics: head yellow except for eyes; postpedicel with long-haired arista (
<figureCitation box="[624,710,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–33" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,605,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[155,1433,597,1547]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–33. Megaphthalmoides japonicus Ozerov. 30, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 31, Male sternite V, ventral view; 32, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 33, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921429/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); thorax yellow with 2 longitudinal stripes on prescutum to scutum; abdominal tergites blackish, covered with hair-like setulae and strong lateral setae; male sternite V posterior lobes which (
<figureCitation box="[301,382,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–33" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,605,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[155,1433,597,1547]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–33. Megaphthalmoides japonicus Ozerov. 30, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 31, Male sternite V, ventral view; 32, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 33, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921429/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) are basally broadened; male surstyli (
<figureCitation box="[815,942,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–33" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1570,1594]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,605,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-204@12.[155,1433,597,1547]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 30–33. Megaphthalmoides japonicus Ozerov. 30, Male postpedicel and pedicel, left lateral view; 31, Male sternite V, ventral view; 32, Male terminalia, left lateral view; 33, Male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921429" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921429/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">Figs 32, 33</figureCitation>
) long and slender, with rows of setulae posteriorly; male cerci clothed with strong setulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,574]" box="[199,581,511,537]" pageId="12" pageNumber="543">
